[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626870&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626870&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

please, hold the pressure here. I don't see any particularly wrong thing
by making sure our workstations (which are used for timesharing more than
the servers) get decent response time from the domain system.

Also, our server machine (bu-it) gets about 99.9999% of the queries, and
handles them just fine. It's also up about 99% of the time.

Do I misunderstand how resolv.conf is supposed to be set up? Does named 
itself use the information from resolv.conf? If not then there may be
no reason to keep the root servers there at all.

--jsol

